v:4 c:$ m:T04-loop-recorder role:dev x:audio/state
gate: LOCKED

task: Record a bar-length phrase of note events and loop it on the shared grid

requires: [FRONTEND_DEV]
out:
  - daww3/experiments/jam-sandbox/src/composables/useLoopRecorder.ts   (new)
  - daww3/experiments/jam-sandbox/src/composables/useJamSession.ts
  - daww3/experiments/jam-sandbox/src/App.vue
  - daww3/experiments/jam-sandbox/src/components/JamControls.vue

depends: [T01-transport-controls, T02-metronome-sync, T03-quantize-notes]

context: |
  THE defining jam-DAW feature: capture a phrase, it loops, everyone layers on
  top. This records NOTE EVENTS (not audio) relative to the loop's beat grid, so
  the loop is portable/quantized (sets up T05 export) and cheap to replay through
  the existing engine.scheduleNoteOn/Off.

  Loop model (note events, beat-relative):
    interface LoopNote { note: number; velocity: number; startBeat: number; durBeats: number }
    interface Loop { lengthBeats: number; bpm: number; division: number; notes: LoopNote[] }

steps:
  1. New composable useLoopRecorder():
     - state: isRecording, isPlaying, loop (Loop | null), loopBars (default 1).
     - startRecording(): mark loop start at the next downbeat (use transport beat);
       capture incoming local notes (note/vel/startBeat from transport.currentBeat,
       durBeats from note off) until lengthBeats reached, then auto-stop + start loop.
     - playLoop(): on each loop cycle, schedule all LoopNotes via engine
       .scheduleNoteOn/off at beatToTime(loopStartBeat + n.startBeat). Re-arm each cycle.
     - stopLoop(), clearLoop().
  2. Hook local notes: feed handleLocalNote's (note,vel,isOn) into the recorder
     when isRecording. Reuse quantize (T03) so recorded starts land on grid.
  3. useJamSession: expose recorder controls; App.vue: route notes; JamControls:
     add a Loop section — Record / Play / Stop / Clear + bars selector + a
     recording/playing indicator. Existing styles.
  4. Loop playback uses the LOCAL peerId so it sounds as "you" (or a dedicated
     loop voice) — decide and keep consistent; do not double-send loop notes to
     the network in this task (local layering first; network loop share is post-MVP).

caution: |
  Keep scope to a SINGLE loop, local playback. Multi-loop, per-peer loop sync,
  and overdub-merge are explicitly out (atomic-logic / one objective).

done:
  - Record arms on downbeat, captures 1 bar of played notes, auto-loops
  - The loop plays back in time with the metronome and repeats cleanly
  - You can play live ON TOP of the looping phrase (layering works)
  - Stop/Clear work; re-record replaces the loop
  - tsc --noEmit passes
